						               													<description>The food wheel is a graphical representation that helps to combine the foods that should be part of your daily diet.&amp;#10;It is a circular symbol that divides into groups of different sizes and gather foods with similar nutritional properties. The purpose of this game is to form sets of cards according to categories of the new food wheel and thus acquire points and win the game.&amp;#10;With the mechanic of card drafting (pick one card from hand to play and pass the remaining cards to next player. Process repeated until last card is played).&amp;#10;Cards are played on the table, in front of each player. This table area it&amp;rsquo;s called &amp;quot;Kitchen&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;There are three types of cards.&amp;#10;Food cards - 7 different colours. The number of cards varies depending on its category. The goal is to collect as many different cards in the same category.&amp;#10;In the end, the cards will also be scored for diversity of categories. Who have more colours gets more points.&amp;#10;Water cards - Light blue cards. The objective is to higher number of cards to gain water points.&amp;#10;Character cards (cooker, waiter and doctor nutritionist) - These are action cards that are played to affect the course of the game.&amp;#10;Once played, these action cards go directly to the trash.&amp;#10;Players canot repeat food cards in his kitchens (repeated cards are sent to the trash) and all the food cards that went to the trash result in an loss of points for that player.&amp;#10;In the end of the game the player with the most number of points wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
